ENTRY       EC 3.4.22.25                Enzyme
NAME        glycyl endopeptidase;
            papaya peptidase B;
            papaya proteinase IV;
            glycine-specific proteinase;
            chymopapain;
            Papaya proteinase 4;
            PPIV;
            chymopapain M
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Cysteine endopeptidases
REACTION    Preferential cleavage: Gly!, in proteins and small molecule substrates
COMMENT     From the papaya plant, Carica papaya. Not inhibited by chicken cystatin, unlike most other homologues of papain, but in peptidase family C1 (papain family)
